reviews.review_text:
horrible end to a wonderful dream a sad show. a once beautiful thing was simply ruined by their popularity once touch of grey/in the dark hit. all day live coverage from the meadowlands parking lot in 87. the shows and set got shorter. there is a set in milwaukee '89 that is 37 minutes ! THEY started doing sing a long classic rock covers. jerry's midi. the corny keyboards. hornsby and his accordion. "light shows" and jumbotron screens. and the throngs of fans. the crowd cheering on the animals as they tear down a fence is just heart breaking. in the monitor feed of this show you can hear jerry say "there's a riot going on out there. let's not dag this on too long. let's get out of here"

a terrible and pathetic end to the dream
